        "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:3:62:2",
        "text": [
          " السَّاحِرُ يُضْرَبُ بِالسَّيْفِ ضَرْبَةً وَاحِدَةً عَلَى [أُمِّ] رَأْسِهِ ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.hubeali": [
            "Muhammad Bin Yahya and Muhammad Bin Al Husayn and Habeeb Bin Al Hassan, from Muhammad Bin Abdul Hameed Al Attar, from Bashar, from Zayd Al Shahham, ",
            "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The sorcerer would be struck with one strike of the sword on top of his head’."
          ]
